<rate>5< /rate>< review>
The absolute best Segway experience! We did a tour a few years ago with a different company in SF. It was great but this was better! Our past experience was a guided tour. We would stop every few minutes during the 1.5 hour tour to wait for the whole group to catch up, then listen to the guide. Fun but not tons of actual riding. Segway SF Bay was a different experience. They made sure our kids (who hadn't ridden before) knew what to do and could handle themselves on the Segway, then they showed us some suggestions for where to ride and let us go. We were able to go at our own pace for the amount of time we chose. We toured through Golden Gate Park, went for ice cream at Polly Ann Ice Cream, then went to Lands End and saw the Golden Gate Bridge. We still had time left on our three hour tour so we were also able to go through the neighborhoods off of Sea Cliff. Such a fantastic time being able to create our own tour and there is nothing like riding Segways! Our girls (14 & 19) said it was the best thing they have ever done on a vacation!</review>

This place is awesome! Their prices are reasonable, the staff is fantastic, and the experience is amazing. The best part is that this is not a tour! You get to go out with your Segway and do whatever you want. My best friend and I cruised through Golden Gate Park and had a blast. One thing to note is that after your rental, walking might seem a bit strange and terribly inefficient :)<//review>

1</rate>
< Review>
If you're thinking about switching to Boost be warned, you are bound for one year. They advertise as a month-to-month service, but your phone is locked for a year. That means, if you decide to switch carriers, you will be unable to do so. I switched to Boost about 5 months ago. I bought a brand new sprint phone, cash, to activate on Boost. Activation went smooth and things were rolling. After some time we were unable to make calls, receive calls, or text from our home. Turns out the network is poor in Mission Viejo and surrounding areas. Eventually the network  stopped responding altogether with one of the phones on the plan. We were forced to go to another provider. We switched to T-Mobile after finding out our phones were compatible. T-mobile sent us the chip to insert into our phones that would activate it on the T-Mobile network. However, because Boost locked our phones we are unable to switch providers. Mind you, I have already paid for T-Mobile service. Now we have no phones to use and told me I have to wait a year to get unlocked. This is a terrible company with even worse coverage. You've been warned.<//Review>

< review>
There's several Ace Hardware's in Redding Anna in the Redding area .
so make sure to use Google and find the one closest to you.
If you're buying a lot for major major projects
We have Lowe's and Home Depot 4 Xtreme projects but for bolts and  sandpaper and what not....little things
don't forget Ace Hardware
they're kind of like 7-Elevens on the corners all over the place.
They don't staff them with a lot of people
but they have a lot of stuff.
so you can generally find what you need,
and if you look hard enough you can always find someone.
the good thing about Ace versus Lowe's or any of the other big box stores is the people generally no a lot of what they're selling they're knowledgeable.< /review>

< Time>
1619742029122<//Time>
<rate>1</rate>< text>
STAY AWAY FROM THIS PLACE, not worth considering it your last option either. It really is very painful to part ways with my therapist who was very capable and caring because of the people from the office. I had been experiencing issues with my insurance lately that were caused by external factors related to bureaucracy. After receiving therapy through their practice for the past 10 months without an issue, they called me from the office the night before my following appointment was due to tell me my insurance rejected their claim for my most recent previous appointment. After a back and forth of phone calls they told me all they could do was cancel my very necessary appointment for the next day and offered to "save me a spot" with my therapist later the next day so I could sort out the issue with my insurance that morning. I understand everyone is struggling during the pandemic, but they really treated me like I was a a foreigner or a criminal of some sort for not being able to pay. They didn't bother offer a financial settlement to avoid interrupting treatment. Keep in mind this was ONE rejected claim out of more than a dozen that had already been processed. They didn't even bother to ask me if I was willing to pay out of pocket for this very necessary care. Upon this interaction, they showed me they weren't interested in my mental health at all, they were only interested in my ability to make my insurance pay them. I know the healthcare system in this country is broken, but regardless of this I have had multiple providers offer me client focused solutions to the problems that I've had with my insurance in the past. This is how I know that other providers are ethical in their practice and are guided by doing as much as they can for their patients' well being. Covenant Behavioral Health's interest in their patients is guided more by how much money they can make out of them. Very unprofessional and unethical business practice to say the least.< /text>

< Text>
I unfortunately had a terrible experience with this post office at two different instances. The first situation occurred when I waited at home for a package that was guaranteed to arrive by 12:00 on a given day and actually arrived at 4 pm. This usually wouldn't be a problem, but the post person dishonestly reported that the package was delivered at 11:15, so the money was not refundable - and it was incredibly time sensitive. Not to mention that I ended up having to take off work because the package was late.

The second instance is even worse. I waited at home again one day to receive a guaranteed priority package. The post person delivered one of my packages, but not the second priority package. They did, however, mark that the package had been delivered, which I know was not true because I was sitting outside when the other package was delivered. I went to the post office two days later (arriving an hour early to make sure I would be able to talk to someone as soon as it opened), and the person behind the counter raised their voice telling me the package hadn't been delivered yet and that I needed to be patient. When he took a deep breath and looked at the tracking information he realized he had read the information incorrectly. Rather than apologize he said, let me get my supervisor. He returned several minutes later saying his supervisor wouldn't talk to me until 9 pm (which didn't work for an individual with work).

I filed a report and attempted to call the post office numerous times, only to be put on hold for hours or not answered. So incredibly frustrating. Especially because I have used USPS for years and never experienced this before. The report I filed was later changed to "Resolved" even though I was not contacted or explained how...

The package is gone, and I will likely never find it.</Text>

I love these guys. I am an eBay seller so I use this location all the time. The job these people do is as impossible as it is thankless. He advised me that their investigator would contact shortly after our conversation, and gave me a direct number in case I needed to contact him at any time.

<Review>Go Falafel Greek Food

Located on the corner of Alpine and Pacific Ave. In Stockton, CA

They do have an IG @Gofalafelgreekfood

Here's our Story;

This review is from January of 2019. I wasn't really writing back then. But I've been inspired since September, 6th of this year. So here goes my review.

So I got this flier about Stockton restaurant week. I checked online and picked out places I was going to take my children.

Asked my youngest Princess if she wanted to come here. She said yeah and threw up the deuce.

Note: There's a reason we (My Children and I)  throw up the peace sign. It's our way of approval or really liking something.

I knew what I wanted right off that bat. I wanted a Gyro. Now I attempted to make them (Gyros) at home, but my Gyros end up looking like a Soft Taco, lol. But the Gyro here, was on point. Especially because I threw some fries inside.

My youngest daughter, ordered Chicken Souvlaki with pita bread. Fries and va bottled water. The chicken Souvlaki is like a chicken skewer or kabob. I'm from the hood and we just call it meat on a stick.  I loved watching her stuff the pita bread with chicken and fries. We always get creative and mix food together on our plate. I  love spending time with my kids.

It's pretty small inside and cozy perfect for a date. Swoon. Bring your boo for a nice one on one.

They do take card and cash. Customer service was pretty good and our food didn't take long.

It was in January and the weather was cold outside and Go Falafel Greek Food hit the spot. Everything always comes together for us. So I did have a memorable moment with my youngest daughter. Good Company And Good Food go hand in hand.

Yes, I'm a fan and definitely be back.

"It only takes a moment to make a moment"

"My children are my world and everything else in life is a bonus"

"Enjoying the simple things in life"

<user_name>Chris Banuelos< /user_name><time>1595697687734< /time><Rate>1</Rate><review>Mr brother and I decided to try the food here for the first time since our usual place Kabob and Gyro House in downtown stockton closed at 7 and doesn't open on weekends. We placed an order online at 6:52pm and we arrived around 7:40pm to pick up the order which said it would be ready 7:14-7:30. When we arrived I told them I was there to pick up an online order and they seemed confused. I let them know that I had ordered through yelp/grubhub, they checked their iPad and then told me my order wasn't ready yet.

I don't think they had any of my order ready and barely started to cook everything after I had arrived. This might not have been their fault but perhaps they weren't paying attention to online orders coming in. This wasn't a huge deal as we weren't in a hurry but I was surprised they hadn't made an order that was placed 40mins ago and the place wasn't even busy. It was almost closing time so I was a bit concerned and hoped that they still had enough fresh ingredients for my order.

When I got home I joked to my family that I hope they cooked everything thoroughly because they had to make everything quickly before closing time. About 3 hours after eating the food I started to get a painful stomach ache and then threw up about five times. I'm pretty sure this food made me sick or gave me food poisoning because it was the only thing I had eaten for several hours and the only food I actually threw up.

The whole ordering experience and ordeal after eating the food and getting sick forces me to give Go Falafel one star. The food itself didn't taste too bad although the portions were a bit overpriced for what you get.

For example the gyro wrap that I got had one piece of tomato, a ton of lettuce and a few strands of meat. Definitely not worth it for the $9 they charge for this item. The usual place i go to charges around $7 for the same item but they put a lot more meat, other veggies and don't stuff it full of mainly lettuce.

I also thought the kabob combo platter was disappointing as they only put like 2 pieces of each meat and the majority of the platter was humus, tzatziki sauce, and a salad. The lettuce in the salad was bitter and the humus was really watery, I'm not sure if they watered it down or what but all the humus I've eaten is usually a bit thicker consistency.

I will never be returning here and will instead be going to Kabob and Gyro House even if I have to wait since they close earlier and on weekends. The quality, hospitality and price at Kabob and Gyro House is so much better and you can even see them cooking your food fresh so you know it's made to order and hygienic.< /review>< pictures>

< rating>
4</rating>
< Text>
Since my wife has begun a plant based diet, we have found it difficult to locate healthy, vegetarian options at restaurants in town. Go Falafel helps us fit that bill quite nicely. Their vegetarian options, particularly their falafel in a pita or on a salad, make the trip very worthwhile. The falafel sandwich is tasty and filled with lettuce,  tomatoes,  onions and the surprising crunch of turnips. Of course, the fried hummus balls round out the whole thing.  I like that the restaurant is close to home and they have a food truck. A very good choice for healthy eating in Stockton.</Text>

<name>T H< /name><Date>1598988729165< /Date><Rate>1<//Rate><text>I had a simple leaking faucet like most people do so I called Dutton Plumbing in Santa Clarita. When the service tech arrived, I explained the problem and symptoms of the leak and showed him that when I applied light downward pressure to the hot water handle, the drip would stop. This guy, without ever looking under the sink or taking the water handle off to inspect the fixture told me that my entire faucet fixture would have to be rebuilt and replace the shut off valves under the sink or only replace the valves. Without inspecting the valves or the faucet itself, he gave a quote for $515 for replacing the valves and $795 for rebuilding the faucet and replacing the valves, both of which I declined as the cost seemed unusually high.

I emailed the company that manufactured the faucet and provided the exact same description of the problem via email that I gave Dutton Plumbingâ€™s service tech in person. The faucet manufacturer replied back suggesting that I replace the seats and springs under the faucet handle and provided me with the part number. I purchased a two pack of the part for $4.98 and a tube of silicone grease for $4.00 at Home Depot and installed them myself in 10 minutes, resulting in the leak being fixed.

Dutton Plumbing not only misdiagnosed how to fix the leak, they suggested work that did not EVEN need to be done at the cost of nearly $800. They do this stuff for a living, so how could they not EVEN suggest replacing the seats and springs? But instead, he told me that I need to replace my entire faucet fixture and valve handles. DO NOT let them do any work until you get a second opinion and estimate. <gmap_id>0x80e82ebed5b30749:0x6a99858c7f6e0140</gmap_id><pics>None< /pics>< text>
We have used Dutton Plumbing for years and have been happy with them until this last guy!  We got a call about a free annual inspection of our water heater and toilets so we had the guy come out to take a look.  At first, he was nice and greeted me outside.
I showed him the water heater, which was in good shape, or so he said.

His disposition seemed to change once he got into the house.  He seemed to be judging us and our house because we are poor and on a fixed income and can not afford nice things. I saw the guy looking around and making faces at our stuff.  I didn't say anything because I thought it was going to end there and I was used to people judging our stuff, which isn't a big deal.

We had 2 of our 3 dogs in a training crate so they wouldn't jump on the guy and knock him down.  He used the word "cage" when he saw them and we corrected him.  I could tell he was judging us, even after we had already explained it to him we did not want them knocking him down and that we had just put them in the crate once we heard the knock on the door.  They are spoiled and well fed, so I had hoped he would have seen that and let it go at that.  He proceded to make rude comments and noises about our house and asked if something on the back of our sons' toilet was pee.  I said I did not know (because it was the toilet our autistic son uses and he sometimes might miss) and hoped he saw embarrassment and humiliation on my face from his comment.  By this point I thought he was just being rude and hostile.  I guess he didn't see the look on my face because he kept going.
The dogs were still barking from a stranger being in the house.  I just walked away from him, told him I was putting and put all the dogs outside so I could hear what he had to say.  I figured he was having a bad day, so I tried to let it go.  I just wanted this over at this point so he could leave.  He quoted us some astronomical price for fixing a running toilet in our bathroom, I thanked him and thought that was the end, but it wasn't.  I figured he just made up the high price because he didnt want to do the work, which was fine by me because I wanted him gone by that time.  I never made faces or said anything to him because I thought he was taking his bad day out on us, but I really felt humiliated and embarrassed.  I was so ready to let it go and move on with my life

It didnt end there though:  About an hour later, we get a knock on the door from Animal Control about how our dogs were in a "cage" all day long, which is not true, and that the lady had to see them and take a picture of them and write up a report!  We have never been so embarrassed and humiliated in all our lives.
We are NEVER using Dutton Plumbing again!  I AM LIVID THAT HE EMBARRASSED US LIKE THAT!  HE WAS UNPROFESSIONAL AND RUDE!  I was trying to let it go, but now I can't.

Never hire this company!  Never!  I could understand if our dogs were emaciated or mangy looking, which they weren't so I dont know why the guy called Animal Control on us!   Our dogs are well taken care of!  Smh!  I  Now, I wish I had said something and kicked him out for being so rude!  Now, there's a report about our dogs on file with Animal Control!  Thanks Dutton Plumbing! I don't know why they hire plumbers like that because he's not people friendly!  I'm calling Corporate on Monday.  I dont care if it is close to Christmas.</text>

< review>
I had a drainage leak beneath my kitchen sink.  I tried fixing it for three days myself but it would not stop leaking. Admitting defeat I called Dutton Plumbing.  They sent on over Steve S. who looked over the situation and gave me an estimate.  Normally I would have gotten three bids but after three days of fighting leaks that trashed my bottom cabinet shelf, I relented figuring if it was good enough for Mom, then go with it.  Steve explained the piping was the PVC pipe, gaskets and slip rings were old and best replaced entirely. After four hours of work, except for the Garbage Disposal, everything was replaced. The leaks stopped. Cost was not cheap but the fix seemed to be working and with a year warranty on their work, I was satisfied. Unfortunately the next day a weep formed under my right sink .  I called Dutton Plumbing and set up another appointment.  They wanted to send Steve out again to repair it but he was diverted for an emergency repair.  However they honored their warranty and sent out Juan P.  who determined another gasket was needed and fixed the issue at no further cost. Jay N. Was my plumber mainly and he was great. Very knowledgeable, friendly, and accommodating of my schedule. I had quite a lot of plumbing work done ( replaced 2 toilets, 2 sinks/ vanities, new kitchen faucet, and replaced main sewer line out to the street.). During all this work, dispatch sent other plumbers, who were also great. I would recommend any of the plumbers. My only problem was with dispatch, who did not seem to comprehend the scope of the work being done on a house built in the 1950's. Dispatch often would schedule Jay to come at 5pm, and he wouldn't be able to make it, as he was on another job and couldn't make it. So, if there was another plumber available they would send them, but that late in the day, it was difficult for them to complete a job. So, I feel that had the dispatcher used better judgement and gave the plumbers extra time to complete a job ( allow for old plumbing - things do go wrong ), my large job could have been done in a more timely manner.</Review>

<userid>110062763213439935022<//userid><Rate>5< /Rate><username>Anna J</username>< Text>
Danny D and Leo B provided service for our residence on a leaking faucet and water pressure regulator. Danny was the main technician and Leo assisted him. Danny was very knowledgable, professional, courteous and friendly. He took time to explain the problem to us, how he planned to approach remedying it and the relative costs. As for expertise and professionalism, their service was excellent. I was especially pleased by Dan's positive professional demeanor. They were prompt, finished the work within the quoted timeframe, explained their process beforehand so we knew exactly what services we were receiving, and they left their workspace as clean as they found it. As for cost, we have worked with less expensive plumbers in the past, so Dutton is not the most competitive provider in terms of pricing, however with Dan's professionalism and a very organized business service model (we have not experienced a more organized effort, from front office to completion), customers can reasonably expect to pay a bit more than what a sole provider/owner-operator would charge that doesn't offer such a comprehensive service model, which includes your initial call, prompt scheduling, phone updates, e-mail updates and accurate time estimations for both technician arrival and work performance. We might have been able to shop around for a cheaper solution since this call was not an emergency call, but overall, we feel we have received value for our dollar.<//Text>

< Text>
Called Dutton office at 7:00 AM, they said someone would be there between 9-11, no problem, then got call saying they would be there in 30 mins, they showed up almost 45 mins, again no problem.

The plumbing problem was a broken PVC pipe in the Meter box, easy to get to.  Well my Father was a plumber and I spent many years helping, so I know whats involved, this is a 15 minute, job 20 if you run into roots.  The guys showed up from Dutton in a nice new van, in pristine white shirts, carrying what looks like a doctors bag. I tried not to laugh out loud, wondering if they realized they were plumbers not doctors.  I told them they would not need all that its a simple pipe repair.   They then took about 10 mins to write up a estimate which was $816.00, but he was very proud that he was able to save me $134.00 and that's how he got it down to $816.00.  I told him he must be mistaken.  When he looked at me as if i was stupid I told him to take his fancy bag get back in his truck and get out of here.  That I am happy to pay a fair price but that was ridiculous and that I hope they don't rip everyone off in the same manner.

BTW Gordan Taylor Plumbing came out right away did the job in about 15 mins.  and I had him tend to a few other issues I had been meaning to fix like my R/O filter system under my sink, check my pressure regulator, test the pressure on the house, check a gas line to my fire pit. WOW I am sure when Dutton would add these other items I would have to take a loan out on the house to pay their bill.  BTW Gordon Taylor Plumbing did the whole job for under $200.00.

The odd thing is the guy from Dutton did not even seem surprised at my response I guess he hears it often.  I never got a call back trying to explain or appologize.  I realize companies are allowed to charge what they like, but at rates like that I am fearful for the people who don't know any better.  I had heard of a senior citizen who had them change a water heater for nearly $3,000.00 and I dismissed it as urban legend as that was just crazy pricing and who would pay such an amount, but now i must wonder if this was a myth.  I have been told their Plumbers work on a commissions.

I have used Dutton before and they were expensive, but this time they were crazy.  They have lost my business and have earned a special place as I will tell everyone of my experiences.  I wonder how many people they actually take advantage of like this.<//Text>
